# Slidev Structure and Layouts Guide

## Layout Types
The presentation template in [temp/slides2.md](mdc:temp/slides2.md) uses several layout types that should be maintained:

- `default`: Standard slide with content
- `section`: Full-page section divider slides
- `two-cols-header`: Split content with header and two columns
- `TwoRowSplit`: Content split into top section and two columns below
- `end`: Final slide for "Thank You" message

## Component Structure
Each slide follows a specific structure:
1. Layout definition (if not default)
2. Heading (# or ## level)
3. Content in appropriate format (text, bullets, images)
4. For multi-column layouts:
   - Use `::left::` and `::right::` markers to define columns
   - Use `::top::` marker in TwoRowSplit layout

## Image Integration
Images should be:
1. Stored in `/image/slides/` directory
2. Referenced using markdown format: `![alt-text](/image/slides/filename.png)`
3. Properly sized for slide context

## Remember
All new presentations should follow this structure but be saved in [slides.md](mdc:slides.md) in the root directory.
